class Solution:
    def canBeEqual(self, s1: str, s2: str) -> bool:
        # Check if characters at even indices and odd indices can be swapped to match
        return sorted(s1[::2]) == sorted(s2[::2]) and sorted(s1[1::2]) == sorted(s2[1::2])
```

This solution works by comparing the characters at even indices and odd indices separately. If the characters at even indices of `s1` can be rearranged to match the characters at even indices of `s2`, and similarly for the odd indices, then `s1` can be made equal to `s2` using the allowed operations.
